 :tx/rationale "CBV AUDIT — checking the 5 tasks for issues. (1) CBV-2 parsing executable patterns is OVERENGINEERED for Stage 1. Running arbitrary braid commands from within braid done creates complexity: shell escaping, timeout handling, error capture, permission issues. SIMPLER: At Stage 1, just do PRESENCE checks — does :harvest/recommended-tasks exist? Does the store have N datoms? Not full command execution. Save command execution for Stage 2. (2) CBV-3 batch close with per-task verification: if braid done t-a t-b t-c and t-b fails verification, what happens? Options: (a) all fail, (b) partial close (a and c close, b stays). ANSWER: partial close is correct — each task is independent. (3) The --defer mode (move to Review status) requires a new TaskStatus variant. This is a schema change (new layer). Keep it simple: defer = just dont close. Agent can braid task set t-xxx status open manually. Cut --defer from CBV-3 to reduce scope. (4) TEST-CBV tests 5 and 6 require actually running braid commands inside tests — integration tests, not unit tests. Separate into unit (1-4,7-10) and integration (5,6). (5) No spec crystallization task for INV-TASK-006. Should add to spec/12-guidance.md or create spec/23-task.md."
